<TITLE> Hospital employee arrested for raping patient's wife </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 2 (bdnews24.com)  Police arrested an employee of the National Institute of Cardiovascular Disease and Hospital Tuesday on charges of raping the wife of a patient. Sub-inspector Faruque Ahmed of Tejgaon Police Station told bdnews24.com Wednesday that the police had arrested laboratory technician Delwar Hossain and his colleague Mozammel Haque. Delwar allegedly raped the 19-year-old wife of Rafiqul Islam of Manikganj, who was undergoing treatment at ward No. 4 on the first floor of the hospital. Quoting the victim, Faruque alleged that Delwar had taken her into the hospital's department store around 9.00pm and raped her after she left the ward to fetch water. Rafiqul Islam has been in hospital from June 24. A case was filed with Tejgaon Police Station. bdnew
